XII. THE SECRET NO ONE KNOWS
Bjorn is the Dragonborn.
He absorbed Sahloknir's soul at Kynesgrove. He absorbed Krosulhah's soul on the road to Riften. He now carries two dragon souls inside a mortal frame that is de-aging in real time. His arthritis is gone. His muscles are hard. The Steed Stone energy is surging back. He is becoming the War-Hound again — or something even more dangerous.
He doesn't know this. He knows he's getting stronger. He knows animals respond to him. He knows the dragonbone shard synced with something inside him. But he doesn't understand the word "Dragonborn." He doesn't know the prophecy. He just knows the universe is telling him he has to be a hero again, and he's terrified.
The Thalmor know a Dragonborn exists. The Dragon Cult knows a Dragonborn exists. Neither knows it's the nice old man with the cart. When they find out, everything changes.
Orion suspects. He said "What if Bjorn is the Dragonborn?" to nobody in particular. Nobody listened.
Davinia saw two dragon souls through Wizard Sight. She said nothing. The Crown's attention sharpened — Ismara recognized something. But Davinia kept the secret.
Bjorn will keep driving the cart, smoking his pipe, cooking stew, and checking on Mila twice before allowing himself to have a drink. He will not seek glory. He will not learn the Thu'um. He will not save the world.
Unless someone he loves is in danger. Then the War-Hound will rise again — and this time, he will not arrive two hours too late.

